<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate";bgcolor="yellow";height="1000" >Vegan Buddha Soup</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 tablespoon olive oil</li>
            <li>1 onion, diced</li>
            <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ground turmeric</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ground cumin</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon smoked paprika</li>
            <li>1 cup carrots, sliced</li>
            <li>1 cup sweet potatoes, diced</li>
            <li>4 cups vegetable broth</li>
            <li>1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed</li>
            <li>1 cup kale or spinach, chopped</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>Cooked quinoa or rice for serving</li>
            <li>Optional toppings: avocado slices, sesame seeds, fresh cilantro</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add diced onions and sauté until translucent.</li>
            <li>Add minced garlic, ground turmeric, ground cumin, and smoked paprika. Stir to combine and sauté for an additional minute.</li>
            <li>Add sliced carrots, diced sweet potatoes, and vegetable broth to the pot. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until the vegetables are tender, about 15-20 minutes.</li>
            <li>Add chickpeas and chopped kale or spinach to the pot. Cook for an additional 5-7 minutes until the greens are wilted.</li>
            <li>Season the soup with salt and black pepper to taste.</li>
            <li>Serve the Vegan Buddha Bowl Soup over cooked quinoa or rice.</li>
            <li>Garnish with optional toppings like avocado slices, sesame seeds, and fresh cilantro.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your nourishing Vegan Buddha Bowl Soup!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

